               <provenance>ʾAminadab is mentioned as the original donor
                     of the Ms. in Additio 1. 
 In a more recent note written in red (Additio
                     2), another person, Walatta Bǝrḥan, appears as the donor, mentioned with her
                     many relatives (?), who are referred to also elsewhere: Walatta Bǝrḥan (1ra, 3vb, 7ra), Walatta Yoḥannǝs (e.g., 1rb, 3vb, 5rc), Walatta ʾAbǝyä-ʾƎgziʾ (e.g., 1rb, 41rc, 64vc), Walatta Mikāʾel (1rc, 4ra, 24vc), Walatta Gabrǝʾel (e.g., 1rc, 25ra, 29rb), ʾabuna Gabra Māryām (2rc, 13ra,
                     44va), ʾabuna Takla Hāymānot (2vc, 153vc, 169vc), Walatta ʾIyasus (e.g., 3rc, 6vb, 55vb), Kǝnfa Mikāʾel (6vc, 173ra), ʾabuna Gabra Śǝllāse
                     (e.g., 7rb, 7va, 49vb), ʾabuna Gabra Takla Hāymānot (e.g., 16rc, 75rb, 80ra), ʾabuna Ḫāyla
                     Śǝllāse (16vb, 17vb, 63va), Kidāna Māryām (17vb, 68va, 74va), Gabra Hǝywät (e.g., 17vb, 24vb, 37rc), Walatta Śǝllāse (e.g., 28rb, 36rb, 100vb), Walatta Madḫǝn (e.g., 31vc, 112rb, 122va), Gabra ʾIyasus (e.g., 36vb, 41rb, 56vc), Walatta Masqal (e.g., 39va, 71ra, 103va), Walatta Māryām (41va), Gabra Tǝnśāʾe (e.g., 42vc, 70vc, 108vb), Walatta ʾƎgziʾ (47va), ʾAmata Māryām (90vb).</provenance></history>
